with the new kid, huh?

253
00:12:11,439 --> 00:12:13,024
And it was going well, too.

254
00:12:13,066 --> 00:12:14,692
Uh, what are you talking about?

255
00:12:14,734 --> 00:12:16,319
I barely even know him.

256
00:12:16,361 --> 00:12:17,737
[STUDENT 1BB]
Oh, for real?

257
00:12:17,779 --> 00:12:19,530
[STUDENT 1AA]
That's not what it looked like.

258
00:12:19,572 --> 00:12:24,535
Hmph. You like him. That's
hilarious. A 3‐D crush.

259
00:12:24,577 --> 00:12:26,788
You're seriously
creepy. What a nerd.

260
00:12:26,829 --> 00:12:28,289
[BOTH laugh]

261
00:12:28,331 --> 00:12:31,376
[KANAKO]
Oh, shut up, dumb pigs.

262
00:12:34,671 --> 00:12:37,048
Go ahead. I'll catch up.

263
00:12:37,090 --> 00:12:39,717
Sure. But make it quick.

264
00:12:39,759 --> 00:12:41,302
Ah.

265
00:12:42,303 --> 00:12:45,348
Hey. I saw you watching
us at practice.

266
00:12:45,390 --> 00:12:46,641
You wanna play soft tennis?

267
00:12:46,683 --> 00:12:49,769
No, I couldn't. I'm really
not athletic at all.

268
00:12:49,811 --> 00:12:51,604
Huh...

269
00:12:56,526 --> 00:12:59,404
Oh, I get it.
You like Toma, right?

270
00:12:59,445 --> 00:13:02,156
Uh! No, that's not it.

271
00:13:02,198 --> 00:13:03,574
Toma is just my
friend, that's all.

272
00:13:03,616 --> 00:13:04,492
It's cool.

273
00:13:04,534 --> 00:13:06,703
‐‐[YUTA] Huh?
‐‐Who you like is who you like.

274
00:13:06,744 --> 00:13:07,578
Uh!

275
00:13:07,620 --> 00:13:10,331
Anyway, you should
join the club.

276
00:13:10,373 --> 00:13:11,416
We need a manager.

277
00:13:11,457 --> 00:13:12,875
Really?

278
00:13:12,917 --> 00:13:15,253
Toma can't take care of
all the equipment alone.

279
00:13:15,295 --> 00:13:17,130
We've got no practice schedule.

280
00:13:17,171 --> 00:13:19,632
Oh. We'll all still
help you with the chores.

281
00:13:19,674 --> 00:13:23,011
It makes sense. It would be
great to have you around.

282
00:13:35,148 --> 00:13:37,191
[AYA]
Mm! That's good.

283
00:13:37,233 --> 00:13:39,694
All right. You've done
enough cooking, Maki.

284
00:13:39,736 --> 00:13:41,195
Come eat.

285
00:13:41,237 --> 00:13:44,532
Yeah, I'm almost done.
This is the last skewer.

286
00:13:44,574 --> 00:13:47,660
Oh, I'm so proud of you,
my little star chef.

287
00:13:47,702 --> 00:13:50,413
Maki. You wanna start
up a <i>yakitori</i> place

288
00:13:50,455 --> 00:13:51,664
after you graduate?

289
00:13:51,706 --> 00:13:54,667
That would cost money, and
it's not like you have any.

290
00:13:54,709 --> 00:13:57,378
Listen, kid. Life isn't
all about money.

291
00:13:57,420 --> 00:13:59,714
Yeah, lots of broke people
say stuff like that.

292
00:13:59,756 --> 00:14:03,468
Hey, that's not funny, you know.

293
00:14:03,509 --> 00:14:04,802
[MAKI]
Should I buy you more beer?

294
00:14:04,844 --> 00:14:06,554
[SHOU] I'm pretty sure
that'd be illegal.

295
00:14:06,596 --> 00:14:09,432
[MAKI] Good point. How
about oolong tea then?

296
00:14:09,474 --> 00:14:10,892
[SHOU]
Yeah.

297
00:14:12,643 --> 00:14:15,104
<i>He</i> hasn't found out
about this place, has he?

298
00:14:15,146 --> 00:14:16,606
I hope not.

299
00:14:16,647 --> 00:14:18,566
I filed for a restraining
order already,

300
00:14:18,608 --> 00:14:19,567
but it takes a while.

301
00:14:19,609 --> 00:14:21,402
It's still going
through the system.

302
00:14:21,444 --> 00:14:24,447
I'm glad that Maki
decided to join a club.

303
00:14:24,489 --> 00:14:27,033
At least he'll be safe
if he's at school.

304
00:14:27,075 --> 00:14:30,578
Hey, Shou. Please listen, I...

305
00:14:30,620 --> 00:14:33,623
[sirens blaring]

306
00:14:35,833 --> 00:14:37,877
Everyone. Yuta Asuka
will be joining

307
00:14:37,919 --> 00:14:40,963
as our manager.
Not your errand boy.

308
00:14:41,005 --> 00:14:43,758
So don't just try to dump
your chores off on him.

309
00:14:43,800 --> 00:14:45,510
You still have to help
keep the storeroom clean

310
00:14:45,551 --> 00:14:47,136
and put away the equipment

311
00:14:47,178 --> 00:14:48,262
Hey, hold up.

312
00:14:48,304 --> 00:14:50,890
I don't remember us making
you the boss, new guy.

313
00:14:50,932 --> 00:14:52,892
But we're all equal members.

314
00:14:52,934 --> 00:14:54,644
Even if I am the new guy.

315
00:14:54,685 --> 00:14:57,438
Maki's right. You guys
should listen to him.

316
00:14:57,480 --> 00:14:58,773
Having a manager
would definitely

317
00:14:58,815 --> 00:14:59,941
make things easier.

318
00:14:59,982 --> 00:15:03,194
Yeah, and doesn't the girls'
team have like five? No fair.

319
00:15:03,236 --> 00:15:04,821
Sure, but that's
because the girls' team

320
00:15:04,862 --> 00:15:07,031
is actually good.

321
00:15:07,073 --> 00:15:11,077
[RINTARO] Okay. Let's head
to the practice grounds.

322
00:15:11,119 --> 00:15:12,578
Why don't we use the courts?

323
00:15:12,620 --> 00:15:14,747
'Cause the boys' team only
gets to use the courts

324
00:15:14,789 --> 00:15:17,083
on Tuesdays, Thursdays,
and Saturdays.

325
00:15:17,125 --> 00:15:19,419
The girls take priority
the rest of the time.

326
00:15:19,460 --> 00:15:22,547
Their team goes to nationals,
like, every year, after all.

327
00:15:22,588 --> 00:15:25,133
Winning teams get
preferential treatment.

328
00:15:25,174 --> 00:15:26,676
It's how the world works, right?

329
00:15:26,717 --> 00:15:29,554
So why doesn't the boys'
team just get good?

330
00:15:29,595 --> 00:15:31,514
Gosh, why didn't
we think of that?

331
00:15:31,556 --> 00:15:32,348
We had a deal.

332
00:15:32,390 --> 00:15:33,182
[SHINGO]
Deal?

333
00:15:33,224 --> 00:15:35,768
Enough talking, guys. Let's go.

334
00:15:41,149 --> 00:15:43,109
[TRACK STUDENT 2AA]
I kinda feel like hurdles today.

335
00:15:43,151 --> 00:15:45,278
Why are you trying
to wreck my legs?

336
00:15:48,406 --> 00:15:51,826
[MAKI] Huh? That's weird.
It's all squishy.

337
00:15:51,868 --> 00:15:55,037
[TAIYO] Yeah. It's a lot softer
than a regular tennis ball.

338
00:15:55,079 --> 00:15:57,582
So it doesn't hurt as
much if it hits you?

339
00:15:57,623 --> 00:16:00,084
Well, it won't do any
permanent damage,

340
00:16:00,126 --> 00:16:02,211
but a really hard hit
can leave a welt.

341
00:16:02,253 --> 00:16:04,338
One time, Tsubasa
landed a big smash

342
00:16:04,380 --> 00:16:06,382
right here on the
inside of my thigh.

343
00:16:06,424 --> 00:16:09,927
and that lump took three
whole days to go away.

344
00:16:09,969 --> 00:16:13,347
[MAKI] And why do all these
balls to look so grimy?

345
00:16:13,389 --> 00:16:15,224
Don't the girls get nice ones?

346
00:16:15,266 --> 00:16:17,560
Yeah, they do. These
ones are actually

347
00:16:17,602 --> 00:16:19,270
the hand‐me‐downs
from the girls.

348
00:16:19,312 --> 00:16:20,271
Huh.

349
00:16:20,313 --> 00:16:22,148
It would be nice to
get to use a fresh one

350
00:16:22,190 --> 00:16:24,775
out of the package with that
white powder coat still on it.

351
00:16:24,817 --> 00:16:26,903
Don't fantasize. It's just sad.

352
00:16:26,944 --> 00:16:29,405
[TOMA]
Maki, let me see your grip.

353
00:16:29,447 --> 00:16:30,656
Okay, here.

354
00:16:30,698 --> 00:16:33,534
Now watch. Here's how
you should do it.

355
00:16:33,576 --> 00:16:37,163
Look at my hand.
Set it like this.

356
00:16:37,205 --> 00:16:39,415
Keep your index
finger right here,

357
00:16:39,457 --> 00:16:42,043
and slide the others
down into a tight grip.

358
00:16:42,084 --> 00:16:43,794
We call this a Western Grip.

359
00:16:43,836 --> 00:16:46,339
Turn it like this and
it's an Eastern Grip.

360
00:16:46,380 --> 00:16:48,049
And holding it in between,

361
00:16:48,090 --> 00:16:50,551
like this, is a
Semi‐Eastern Grip.

362
00:16:50,593 --> 00:16:53,221
Western Grip is standard
in soft tennis.

363
00:16:53,262 --> 00:16:54,347
I see.

364
00:16:54,388 --> 00:16:55,640
You try it.

365
00:16:57,725 --> 00:17:00,520
'Kay. How's this?

366
00:17:02,688 --> 00:17:03,940
Watch where you're swinging.

367
00:17:03,981 --> 00:17:04,774
Uh, my bad.

368
00:17:04,815 --> 00:17:05,900
Be careful.

369
00:17:05,942 --> 00:17:07,318
Check your surroundings
before you start

370
00:17:07,360 --> 00:17:08,486
practicing your swing.

371
00:17:08,528 --> 00:17:09,779
You don't wanna hit anybody.

372
00:17:09,820 --> 00:17:11,864
Right. Got it.

373
00:17:11,906 --> 00:17:13,783
[TOMA] And you don't just
wave it around like that.

374
00:17:13,824 --> 00:17:15,576
Wait, like what?

375
00:17:15,618 --> 00:17:17,578
Watch me. Look at my posture.

376
00:17:17,620 --> 00:17:18,955
Right, I'm watching.

377
00:17:18,996 --> 00:17:21,999
Like this. Here's the soft
tennis resting stance.

378
00:17:22,041 --> 00:17:23,668
Keep your knees slightly bent.

379
00:17:23,709 --> 00:17:25,545
Put your weight on the
balls of your feet.

380
00:17:25,586 --> 00:17:26,921
Why's that?

381
00:17:26,963 --> 00:17:28,965
Humans can't react quickly
with their knees locked

382
00:17:29,006 --> 00:17:30,466
and their heels on the ground,

383
00:17:30,508 --> 00:17:32,260
it takes too long to get moving.

384
00:17:32,301 --> 00:17:33,886
You never know which
part of the court

385
00:17:33,928 --> 00:17:36,681
the ball's gonna go to,
but you still have to be able

386
00:17:36,722 --> 00:17:38,933
to make it there. Make sense?

387
00:17:38,975 --> 00:17:42,061
Yeah, it does make sense.
I'd kinda forgotten.

388
00:17:44,772 --> 00:17:46,524
[TOMA] Now you're going
to plant your left foot

389
00:17:46,566 --> 00:17:48,150
forward for the backswing.

390
00:17:48,192 --> 00:17:50,152
Then twist your whole body.

391
00:17:50,194 --> 00:17:53,531
Don't just use your arms;
turn your hips into the swing.

392
00:17:53,573 --> 00:17:56,450
Open the face of the racket
to hit the ball dead on.

393
00:17:56,492 --> 00:17:58,202
Make sure to get a clean hit.

394
00:17:58,244 --> 00:17:59,662
And as the ball makes contact,

395
00:17:59,704 --> 00:18:02,081
follow through with the
motion, whip your wrist,

396
00:18:02,123 --> 00:18:04,458
and let the racket keep going
over your left shoulder

397
00:18:04,500 --> 00:18:07,837
just like this, and step
through with the right foot.

398
00:18:07,878 --> 00:18:10,006
I think I get it.

399
00:18:14,760 --> 00:18:15,886
Like that?

400
00:18:15,928 --> 00:18:17,388
Good job. Nice form.

401
00:18:17,430 --> 00:18:19,307
That was a forehand stroke.

402
00:18:19,348 --> 00:18:20,391
'Kay, got it.

403
00:18:20,433 --> 00:18:22,101
Now, let's see you hit a ball.

404
00:18:22,143 --> 00:18:24,895
[gasps] Already?

405
00:18:24,937 --> 00:18:26,022
[TOMA grunts]

406
00:18:33,779 --> 00:18:34,864
Maki, hit this.

407
00:18:34,905 --> 00:18:36,032
Me?

408
00:18:39,160 --> 00:18:41,662
He's never even held
a racket before.

409
00:18:47,460 --> 00:18:48,628
[BOTH gasp]

410
00:18:48,669 --> 00:18:50,004
You're kidding.

411
00:18:52,214 --> 00:18:53,591
Awesome.

412
00:18:57,261 --> 00:18:58,596
Is this really his first time?

413
00:18:58,638 --> 00:19:00,139
There's no way.

414
00:19:04,060 --> 00:19:06,103
Ah‐‐

415
00:19:06,145 --> 00:19:07,104
My bad.

416
00:19:07,146 --> 00:19:10,858
It's a good start though.
Now time for the backhand.

417
00:19:10,900 --> 00:19:12,693
You'll use this to hit a ball
that's coming at you

418
00:19:12,735 --> 00:19:13,986
from your left side.

419
00:19:14,028 --> 00:19:15,029
Why's that?

420
00:19:15,071 --> 00:19:16,656
Couldn't I just
change my position

421
00:19:16,697 --> 00:19:18,991
so that I can get to
it with my right hand?

422
00:19:19,033 --> 00:19:20,451
He's got a point.

423
00:19:20,493 --> 00:19:21,827
Yeah, but it's slow.

424
00:19:21,869 --> 00:19:23,496
You'd be making
yourself move farther,

425
00:19:23,537 --> 00:19:25,539
and you'll never
hit any fast balls.

426
00:19:25,581 --> 00:19:27,958
[BOTH gasp]

427
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:30,044
Plant your right foot
in front of you.

428
00:19:30,086 --> 00:19:32,171
Your backswing should
look like this.

429
00:19:32,213 --> 00:19:33,839
Then turn your wrist this way.

430
00:19:33,881 --> 00:19:35,925
Now you give it a shot.

431
00:19:35,966 --> 00:19:36,884
Like this?

432
00:19:36,926 --> 00:19:39,136
And then when you see
the ball is approaching,

433
00:19:39,178 --> 00:19:42,056
swing so that it lands flush
on the racket's face.

434
00:19:42,098 --> 00:19:46,644
Hit the ball dead on,
just like with the forehand.

435
00:19:46,686 --> 00:19:48,938
You mean like this.

436
00:19:48,979 --> 00:19:50,815
Don't forget to follow through.

437
00:19:50,856 --> 00:19:53,651
See? Open your stance.

438
00:19:55,695 --> 00:19:56,737
How's that?

439
00:19:56,779 --> 00:19:59,448
Not bad. Show me one more.

440
00:19:59,490 --> 00:20:01,409
[MAKI]
Like this.

441
00:20:05,705 --> 00:20:08,457
Dang, I guess that's what
I should've been doing.

442
00:20:08,499 --> 00:20:10,459
I forgot the fundamentals.

443
00:20:14,130 --> 00:20:15,423
Oh.

444
00:20:16,882 --> 00:20:18,467
[meows]

445
00:20:28,602 --> 00:20:31,439
Wow, Katsuragi.
You're something else.

446
00:20:43,701 --> 00:20:45,494
Sorry, that one
got away from me.

447
00:20:45,536 --> 00:20:47,955
You okay Katsuragi?

448
00:20:47,997 --> 00:20:50,708
What's the matter?

449
00:20:50,750 --> 00:20:52,001
I don't get it.

450
00:20:52,042 --> 00:20:55,337
A whole year and this is the
best you guys can do. Really?

451
00:20:55,379 --> 00:20:56,297
[BOTH]
Huh?

452
00:20:56,338 --> 00:20:58,424
Hold up. You're
talking like that

453
00:20:58,466 --> 00:20:59,800
just cuz you can hit the ball?

454
00:20:59,842 --> 00:21:01,552
Well, it seems like
even that's too much

455
00:21:01,594 --> 00:21:03,846
for some of you.
What's up with that?

456
00:21:03,888 --> 00:21:06,015
Look, we just suck
at soft tennis, okay?

457
00:21:06,056 --> 00:21:07,725
It's not like
anyone really cares.

458
00:21:07,767 --> 00:21:10,853
Are you sure? I bet you
suck at other stuff, too.

459
00:21:10,895 --> 00:21:11,896
[BOTH growl]

460
00:21:11,937 --> 00:21:13,481
Yeah. People who
suck at everything

461
00:21:13,522 --> 00:21:15,149
get really good
at making excuses.

462
00:21:15,191 --> 00:21:20,446
Hey. That's enough!
Stop talking.

463
00:21:20,488 --> 00:21:22,615
This is why you
can't win a match.

464
00:21:22,656 --> 00:21:25,493
You won't get results if
you don't put in the effort.

465
00:21:25,534 --> 00:21:27,328
That should be obvious.

466
00:21:27,369 --> 00:21:29,914
It's why you guys are
such a loser club.

467
00:21:29,955 --> 00:21:32,708
Just clowns and cowards,
too scared to try.

468
00:21:32,750 --> 00:21:34,543
[gasps] You jerk!

469
00:21:34,585 --> 00:21:39,423
[TAIYO] Don't say that. Don't
call us cowards. It's not true!

470
00:21:39,465 --> 00:21:41,926
What's crying
gonna do? Come on.

471
00:21:41,967 --> 00:21:44,553
We can do better if we try.
So why would you say‐‐

472
00:21:44,595 --> 00:21:47,139
Failures always say
stuff like that, too.

473
00:21:47,181 --> 00:21:48,557
[TSUBASA]
That's enough!

474
00:21:51,143 --> 00:21:54,313
You wanna hit me?
Use your fists.

475
00:21:57,608 --> 00:22:00,236
[TSUBASA] Waste of time
to hit a guy like you.

476
00:22:00,277 --> 00:22:02,988
Hey, Rintaro, why don't we
work on practice swings?

477
00:22:03,030 --> 00:22:04,240
[gasps]

478
00:22:04,281 --> 00:22:07,660
Uh. Right. Guys.
Get in a line.

479
00:22:07,701 --> 00:22:10,746
Twenty swings,
Tsubasa counts first!

480
00:22:10,788 --> 00:22:13,541
[TSUBASA]
One!

481
00:22:13,582 --> 00:22:16,293
Two!

482
00:22:16,335 --> 00:22:19,338
Three!

483
00:22:19,380 --> 00:22:22,132
Four!

484
00:22:22,174 --> 00:22:24,552
Five!

485
00:22:24,593 --> 00:22:26,345
‐‐What was that?
‐‐[TSUBASA] Six!

486
00:22:28,347 --> 00:22:29,849
What was what?

487
00:22:31,308 --> 00:22:32,518
‐‐[TSUBASA] Seven!
‐‐[KEI] Hey, Namie,

488
00:22:32,560 --> 00:22:34,520
has your brother
told you anything?

489
00:22:34,562 --> 00:22:37,022
All he said was that someone
new joined the club.

490
00:22:37,064 --> 00:22:39,525
Ah. This seems like
it could be fun.

491
00:22:39,567 --> 00:22:40,901
You think so?

492
00:22:40,943 --> 00:22:42,486
[meows]

493
00:22:42,528 --> 00:22:43,904
[KANAKO]
How boring.

494
00:22:43,946 --> 00:22:45,865
It looked like there
was gonna be a fight.

495
00:22:45,906 --> 00:22:46,991
What a letdown.

496
00:22:47,032 --> 00:22:49,910
[TSUBASA]
Twelve!

497
00:22:49,952 --> 00:22:52,830
Thirteen!

498
00:22:52,872 --> 00:22:57,293
Fourteen! Fifteen!

